# Normalize all text files to LF in the repository and in the working tree.
#
# Without this, a Windows checkout under core.autocrlf=true rewrites source
# files to CRLF. The sync transforms pass the body through verbatim, so they
# then emit CRLF-bodied output that differs byte-for-byte from the committed
# LF artifacts — `npm run sync` reports spurious diffs and CI's clean-tree
# check would be impossible to satisfy from Windows. Forcing LF everywhere
# keeps sync byte-deterministic across platforms. Git auto-detects binary
# files (text=auto) and leaves them untouched; this repo has none today.
* text=auto eol=lf
